draw_text(info3_x, info3_y, "Irish traditional music has endured against the forces\nof modern media better than the indigenous folk music\nof most European countries, and is still widely performed\ntoday. While many songs are sung in English, some are\nsung in Gaelic, the ancient language of the Celtic people\nin what is now Ireland and Scotland. The most distinct\nmusical instruments used in Irish folk music are fiddles\nand flutes, which lends the music an upbeat tempo.");